* Iris glared out into the ash, reading her senses as well as her systems.
It was differnet now then it ever was before, having a body to fight with 
instead of using an entire base as your weapon.
Different.
But, there was little time to think and a whole lot of it to act.
Iris removed an armored rifle from her waist in two halves and snapped them 
together, arming it and aiming towards the first to come into her range, Sun 
Crusher.
Pulling the trigger she fored 6 charges towards him, but in a design that 
could hit him on any area of his body.*
